Rating: 3
I would say this receipe would easily serve twice as many people if it is served as part of a roast dinner with veg. As an earlier review said, what's not to love about potatoes, mushrooms and butter? I used half and half (rather than milk). I also made both the potatoes and mushrooms in the morning. I chilled the mushrooms and gently reheated them before mixing them with the potatoes. I put the potates throgh a ricer once they had been cooked and then covered them and left them at room temperature until I was ready to serve. I reheated the potatoes, added the mushrooms and voila!

Rating: 4
